    <h2>Knobs</h2>
  </header>

	<p><strong>Knob links</strong> double as compact navigation chips: they keep menus tidy, highlight filters, and make icon/text pairings feel intentional. Use them when you need a tappable control that still behaves like a link&mdash;opening detail panes, swapping content, or filtering tables&mdash;so you gain the styling nuance without sacrificing <em>semantic anchors</em>.</p>

  <div class="section-example">
    <a class="knob">Knob link</a><br>
    <a class="knob hover">Knob hover link</a><br>
    <a class="knob focus">Knob focused link</a><br>
    <a class="knob active">Knob active link</a><br>
    <a class="knob">
      <svg class="icon">
        <use xlink:href="/images/icons.svg#star"></use>
      </svg> 
      Knob icon link
    </a>
	</div>
  
  <div class="code-example">
    <pre><code>&lt;a class="knob"&gt;...&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class="knob hover"&gt;...&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class="knob focus"&gt;...&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class="knob active"&gt;...&lt;/a&gt;</code></pre>
  </div>

