<section>
  <header>
    <h2>Buttons</h2>
  </header>
	<p><strong>Button links</strong> mimic native buttons for times when a navigation target needs the prominence of a primary call-to-action but still routes to another page. Lean on these when a surface lacks room for both buttons and links, and review the <a href="/documentation/elements/buttons">buttons</a> guidelines to stay aligned on spacing, color choices, and <em>interactive etiquette</em>.</p>

	<div class="section-example">
    <a class="button">Button link</a><br>
    <a class="button hover">Button hover link</a><br>
    <a class="button focus">Button focused link</a><br>
    <a class="button active">Button active link</a>
  </div>
  
  <div class="code-example">
    <pre><code>&lt;a class="button"&gt;...&lt;/a&gt;
